This epistle was evidently written to Maecenas to justify himself for preferring considerations of -health to the claims of his patron. He had apparently retired from the city to the country (perhaps to Tibur. 5. dum ficus, etc.: a poetical description of the unhealthy season of autumn.

6. dissignatorem, the under- taker‚ who managed funereus, much as in modern times—decorat: of course the presence of the lictors, as “assistant marshals,” would in- dicate a splendid funeral, and so they are said to be the undertaker’s adommentS. — atris : clothed in black, as in modern times.
